ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.28                 Enzyme
NAME        ent-cassa-12,15-diene synthase;
            OsDTC1;
            OsKS7
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     ent-copalyl-diphosphate diphosphate-lyase (ent-cassa-12,15-diene-forming)
REACTION    ent-copalyl diphosphate = ent-cassa-12,15-diene + diphosphate [RN:R09119]
ALL_REAC    R09119
SUBSTRATE   ent-copalyl diphosphate [CPD:C06089]
PRODUCT     ent-cassa-12,15-diene [CPD:C18226];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     This class I diterpene cyclase produces ent-cassa-12,15-diene, a precursor of the rice phytoalexins (-)-phytocassanes A-E. Phytoalexins are diterpenoid secondary metabolites that are involved in the defense mechanism of the plant, and are produced in response to pathogen attack through the perception of elicitor signal molecules such as chitin oligosaccharide, or after exposure to UV irradiation.
HISTORY     EC 4.2.3.28 created 2008
